<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="bg-mist-100">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content={get_csrf_token()} />
    <title>Cinegraph — Film discovery is broken. Their agenda is not yours.</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Every mainstream movie rating is owned by someone who profits from your answer — and rigged by bots. Cinegraph is independent, evidence-based, and has nothing to sell you."
    />
    <link
      rel="icon"
      href="data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 24 24'%3E%3Crect x='2' y='2' width='20' height='20' rx='4' fill='%2314120f'/%3E%3Cpath d='M7 12 L11 8 L15 14 L17 11' fill='none' stroke='white' stroke-width='1.6' stroke-linecap='round' stroke-linejoin='round'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"
    />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin="anonymous" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=Inter:ital,opsz,wght@0,14..32,100..900;1,14..32,100..900&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
    />
    <link phx-track-static rel="stylesheet" href={~p"/assets/oatmeal.css"} />
    <noscript>
      <style>
        /* No-JS fallback: `.reveal` is opacity:0 until JS adds `.in` via
           IntersectionObserver — without this, no-JS visitors see blank blocks. */
        .reveal { opacity: 1 !important; transform: none !important; }
      </style>
    </noscript>
    <style>
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; scroll-padding-top: 5rem; }

      /* JetBrains Mono for the few mono labels (oatmeal.css has no mono mapping) */
      .font-mono { font-family: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; }

      /* Film-grain noise — lifted from the Cinegraph Oatmeal theme */
      .grain {
        background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D'http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg'%20width%3D'250'%20height%3D'250'%20viewBox%3D'0%200%20100%20100'%3E%3Cfilter%20id%3D'n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence%20type%3D'turbulence'%20baseFrequency%3D'1.4'%20numOctaves%3D'1'%20seed%3D'2'%20stitchTiles%3D'stitch'%20result%3D'n'%2F%3E%3CfeComponentTransfer%20result%3D'g'%3E%3CfeFuncR%20type%3D'linear'%20slope%3D'4'%20intercept%3D'1'%2F%3E%3CfeFuncG%20type%3D'linear'%20slope%3D'4'%20intercept%3D'1'%2F%3E%3CfeFuncB%20type%3D'linear'%20slope%3D'4'%20intercept%3D'1'%2F%3E%3C%2FfeComponentTransfer%3E%3CfeColorMatrix%20type%3D'saturate'%20values%3D'0'%20in%3D'g'%2F%3E%3C%2Ffilter%3E%3Crect%20width%3D'100%25'%20height%3D'100%25'%20filter%3D'url(%23n)'%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E");
        background-position: center;
      }

      /* Scroll-reveal */
      .reveal { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); transition: opacity .6s cubic-bezier(.2,.6,.2,1), transform .6s cubic-bezier(.2,.6,.2,1); }
      .reveal.in { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .reveal { opacity:1; transform:none; transition:none; } }

      /* Marquee */
      @keyframes marquee { from { transform: translateX(0); } to { transform: translateX(-50%); } }
      .marquee-track { display: flex; width: max-content; animation: marquee 38s linear infinite; }
      .marquee-slow .marquee-track { animation-duration: 60s; }
      .marquee:hover .marquee-track { animation-play-state: paused; }
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .marquee-track { animation: none; } }

      /* Wordmark base — typographic logo stand-ins (editorial use) */
      .wm { font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -.02em; white-space: nowrap; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: .28em; line-height: 1; }
      .wm-imdb-badge { background:#F5C518; color:#000; border-radius:4px; padding:.12em .34em; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-.03em; }
      .wm-dot { width:.42em; height:.42em; border-radius:9999px; display:inline-block; }

      /* Provenance bars */
      .prov-fill { width: 0; transition: width 1.1s cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.2,1); }
      .prov.in .prov-fill { width: var(--w); }

      /* Citation tooltip */
      .cite-pop { opacity:0; visibility:hidden; transform: translateY(4px); transition: opacity .14s, transform .14s; }
      .cite-host:hover .cite-pop, .cite-host:focus-within .cite-pop { opacity:1; visibility:visible; transform: translateY(0); }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-mist-100 text-mist-950 font-sans antialiased">
    <!-- ============================ NAV ============================ -->
    <header class="sticky top-0 z-30 bg-mist-100/[0.92] backdrop-blur-md border-b border-mist-950/10">
      <div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-2xl items-center gap-4 px-6 py-[14px] md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10">
        <a href="#top" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 no-underline">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="20" rx="4" class="fill-mist-950" />
            <path
              d="M7 12 L11 8 L15 14 L17 11"
              fill="none"
              stroke="#fff"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
            />
            <circle cx="7" cy="12" r="1.4" fill="#fff" /><circle
              cx="11"
              cy="8"
              r="1.4"
              fill="#fff"
            />
            <circle cx="15" cy="14" r="1.4" fill="#fff" /><circle
              cx="17"
              cy="11"
              r="1.4"
              fill="#fff"
            />
          </svg>
          <span class="text-[19px] font-semibold tracking-[-.018em] text-mist-950">
            Cinegraph
          </span>
        </a>
        <nav class="ml-3 hidden gap-[2px] md:flex">
          <a
            href="#ownership"
            class="rounded-md px-3 py-[7px] text-[13.5px] font-medium text-mist-700 no-underline hover:text-mist-950"
          >
            Who owns it
          </a>
          <a
            href="#scoreboard"
            class="rounded-md px-3 py-[7px] text-[13.5px] font-medium text-mist-700 no-underline hover:text-mist-950"
          >
            The scoreboard
          </a>
          <a
            href="#different"
            class="rounded-md px-3 py-[7px] text-[13.5px] font-medium text-mist-700 no-underline hover:text-mist-950"
          >
            How we differ
          </a>
        </nav>
        <div class="ml-auto flex items-center gap-2">
          <a
            href="/auth/login"
            class="hidden h-[34px] items-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-[7px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 px-3 text-[12.5px] font-semibold text-mist-950 no-underline hover:bg-mist-950/[0.04] sm:inline-flex"
          >
            Sign in
          </a>
          <a
            href="/movies"
            class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-mist-950 px-3.5 py-1.5 text-[13px] font-medium text-mist-100 no-underline hover:bg-mist-800"
          >
            Explore films
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="top" class="overflow-clip">
      <!-- ============================ HERO — PARADOX ============================ -->
      <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-mist-950 text-white">
        <div class="grain pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.06] mix-blend-screen">
        </div>
        <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(120%_120%_at_50%_-10%,rgba(253,79,0,0.10),transparent_55%)]">
        </div>

        <div class="relative">
          <!-- streaming logo wall (marquee) -->
          <div class="border-b border-white/10 py-5">
            <div class="marquee marquee-slow relative overflow-hidden [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,transparent,#000_8%,#000_92%,transparent)]">
              <div class="marquee-track items-center gap-12 pr-12 text-white/45">
                <span class="wm text-[19px]" style="color:#E50914">NETFLIX</span>
                <span class="wm text-[17px]">
                  prime <span class="font-light opacity-70">video</span>
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[22px] font-extrabold tracking-[-.04em]">max</span>
                <span class="wm text-[18px]">Disney<span style="color:#3fb7ff">+</span></span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">
                  tv<span class="opacity-60">+</span>
                  <span class="font-normal opacity-60">Apple</span>
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[18px]" style="color:#1ce783">hulu</span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">Paramount<span style="color:#0064ff">+</span></span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">peacock</span>
                <span class="wm font-display text-[22px] not-italic" style="letter-spacing:.18em">
                  MUBI
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[15px] tracking-[.34em] font-semibold">CRITERION</span>
                <span class="wm text-[14px] font-medium italic text-white/35">
                  …and a dozen more
                </span>
                <!-- duplicate for seamless loop -->
                <span class="wm text-[19px]" style="color:#E50914">NETFLIX</span>
                <span class="wm text-[17px]">
                  prime <span class="font-light opacity-70">video</span>
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[22px] font-extrabold tracking-[-.04em]">max</span>
                <span class="wm text-[18px]">Disney<span style="color:#3fb7ff">+</span></span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">
                  tv<span class="opacity-60">+</span>
                  <span class="font-normal opacity-60">Apple</span>
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[18px]" style="color:#1ce783">hulu</span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">Paramount<span style="color:#0064ff">+</span></span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px]">peacock</span>
                <span class="wm font-display text-[22px] not-italic" style="letter-spacing:.18em">
                  MUBI
                </span>
                <span class="wm text-[15px] tracking-[.34em] font-semibold">CRITERION</span>
                <span class="wm text-[14px] font-medium italic text-white/35">
                  …and a dozen more
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-6 py-20 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10 lg:py-28">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.2em] text-white/55">
              The paradox
            </div>
            <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-5xl text-balance font-display text-[44px] leading-[1.02] tracking-[-.02em] sm:text-[64px] lg:text-[78px]">
              It's never been <em class="text-brand not-italic">easier</em>
              to watch a film.<br class="hidden sm:block" /> It's never been
              <em class="not-italic underline decoration-white/30 underline-offset-[6px]">
                harder
              </em>
              to find a good one.
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-[16px] leading-relaxed text-white/80 sm:text-[18px]">
              A century of cinema, one tap away — and 40 minutes of scrolling later, you settle for the same sequel everyone else did.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-white/55">
              They solved distribution. They broke discovery.
              <span class="text-white">Cinegraph is the choosing part.</span>
            </p>
            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
              <a
                href="/movies"
                class="inline-flex h-11 items-center rounded-[7px] bg-white px-5 text-[14px] font-semibold text-mist-950 no-underline hover:bg-mist-50"
              >
                Find something great →
              </a>
              <a
                href="#different"
                class="inline-flex h-11 items-center rounded-[7px] border border-white/20 px-5 text-[14px] font-semibold text-white no-underline hover:bg-white/10"
              >
                See how we're different
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
<!-- ============================ ANALOGY BAND ============================ -->
      <section class="border-b border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50">
        <div class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-2xl items-center gap-10 px-6 py-16 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:px-10 lg:py-20">
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-mist-500">
              The conflict of interest
            </div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 max-w-xl font-display text-[34px] italic leading-[1.08] tracking-[-.01em] text-mist-950 sm:text-[46px]">
              It's the restaurant writing its own reviews.
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-5 max-w-xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
              Amazon owns IMDb <em class="italic">and</em>
              makes the movies. Asking IMDb whether an Amazon film is good is asking the restaurant to rate its own kitchen. The scoreboard isn't neutral — it's a player who also keeps score.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-5 font-display text-[22px] italic text-mist-950">
              They aren't a referee. They're a player who also keeps score.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div class="rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-100 p-5">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-mist-500">
                Their kitchen
              </div>
              <div class="mt-3 font-display text-[40px] italic leading-none text-mist-950">
                ★★★★★
              </div>
              <p class="mt-3 text-[12.5px] leading-snug text-mist-600">
                The rating is marketing wearing a referee's jersey.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-950 p-5 text-white">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-white/50">
                Cinegraph
              </div>
              <div class="mt-3 font-display text-[40px] italic leading-none">Evidence</div>
              <p class="mt-3 text-[12.5px] leading-snug text-white/65">
                No kitchen to protect. No film to push. Nothing to sell you.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
<!-- ============================ OWNERSHIP WALL ============================ -->
      <section id="ownership" class="scroll-mt-20 border-b border-mist-950/10 py-16 lg:py-24">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-6 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10">
          <div class="reveal max-w-3xl">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-mist-500">
              Follow the money
            </div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-[34px] italic leading-[1.08] tracking-[-.01em] text-mist-950 sm:text-[48px]">
              Who really owns your movie ratings?
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
              Every mainstream rating platform answers to either a mega-corporation that <em class="italic">sells you the movie</em>, or to Wall Street money that
              <em class="italic">cashes out on the exit.</em>
              Read it top to bottom: owned, owned, owned — for sale. Then one clean break.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal mt-10">
            <!-- Mega-corp bucket -->
            <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="text-[18px]">🏢</span>
              <h3 class="text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-mist-900">
                Captured by mega-corporations
              </h3>
              <span class="text-[12.5px] text-mist-500">— they make &amp; sell the movies</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 px-5 py-4">
                <span class="wm text-[20px] text-mist-950">
                  <span class="wm-imdb-badge">IMDb</span>
                </span>
                <span class="text-mist-300">──►</span>
                <span class="wm text-[16px] text-mist-700">
                  amazon<span class="text-brand">.</span>
                </span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 px-5 py-4">
                <span class="wm text-[15px] text-mist-950">
                  <span class="wm-dot" style="background:#FA320A"></span>Rotten Tomatoes
                </span>
                <span class="text-mist-300">──►</span>
                <span class="wm text-right text-[13px] leading-tight text-mist-700">
                  Comcast / NBCU<br />+ Warner Bros.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 px-1 text-[12.5px] italic text-mist-500">
              These owners profit when you watch <em>their</em> movie.
            </p>
            
<!-- PE bucket -->
            <div class="mb-3 mt-8 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="text-[18px]">💰</span>
              <h3 class="text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-mist-900">
                Captured by private equity / Wall St.
              </h3>
              <span class="text-[12.5px] text-mist-500">— they cash out on the exit</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 px-5 py-4">
                <span class="wm text-[16px] text-mist-950">
                  <span class="inline-block h-3 w-3 rounded-[2px]" style="background:#ffcc34">
                  </span><span
                    class="inline-block h-3 w-3 rounded-[2px]"
                    style="background:#66cc33"
                  ></span><span
                    class="inline-block h-3 w-3 rounded-[2px]"
                    style="background:#fc4f30"
                  ></span>
                  Metacritic
                </span>
                <span class="text-mist-300">──►</span>
                <span class="wm text-right text-[13px] leading-tight text-mist-700">
                  Fandom, Inc.<br />
                  <span class="text-[11px] text-mist-500">
                    ◂ Red Ventures (PE)
                  </span>
                </span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-brand/40 bg-brand/[0.05] px-5 py-4">
                <span class="wm text-[15px] text-mist-950">
                  <span class="wm-dot" style="background:#FF8000"></span><span
                    class="wm-dot"
                    style="background:#00E054"
                  ></span><span class="wm-dot" style="background:#40BCF4"></span>
                  Letterboxd
                </span>
                <span class="text-mist-300">──►</span>
                <span class="wm text-right text-[12.5px] leading-tight text-mist-700">
                  Tiny ──► <span class="font-bold text-brand">FOR SALE</span>
                  <br /><span class="text-[11px] text-mist-500">PE, 2026</span>
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 px-1 text-[12.5px] italic text-mist-500">
              These owners profit when the <em>asset</em>
              sells. Your taste is engagement to be flipped.
            </p>
            
<!-- chant -->
            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 font-display text-[22px] italic text-mist-400">
              <span>owned.</span><span>owned.</span><span>owned.</span><span class="text-brand">for sale.</span>
            </div>
            
<!-- the break -->
            <div class="mt-8 border-t border-dashed border-mist-950/20 pt-8">
              <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="text-[18px]">🌱</span>
                <h3 class="text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-mist-900">
                  Open · no film business · no conflict
                </h3>
              </div>
              <div class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 px-5 py-4">
                  <span class="wm text-[15px] text-mist-950">
                    TMDb <span class="text-[11px] font-medium text-mist-500">(our data)</span>
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-mist-300">──►</span>
                  <span class="wm text-right text-[12.5px] leading-tight text-mist-700">
                    Xperi / TiVo<br />
                    <span class="text-[11px] text-mist-500">
                      metadata co · open data
                    </span>
                  </span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-[10px] border border-mist-950 bg-mist-950 px-5 py-4 text-white">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
                    <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                      <rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="20" rx="4" fill="#fff" /><path
                        d="M7 12 L11 8 L15 14 L17 11"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="#14120f"
                        stroke-width="1.6"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                      /><circle cx="7" cy="12" r="1.4" fill="#14120f" /><circle
                        cx="11"
                        cy="8"
                        r="1.4"
                        fill="#14120f"
                      /><circle cx="15" cy="14" r="1.4" fill="#14120f" /><circle
                        cx="17"
                        cy="11"
                        r="1.4"
                        fill="#14120f"
                      />
                    </svg>
                    <span class="wm text-[15px]">Cinegraph</span>
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-white/30">──►</span>
                  <span class="text-right text-[12.5px] leading-tight text-white/80">
                    Independent. Unaligned.<br />
                    <span class="text-white/55">
                      Nothing to sell you.
                    </span>
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="mt-6 font-display text-[28px] italic text-mist-950">
                Your agenda is not theirs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-[12.5px] leading-relaxed text-mist-500">
            The dividing line isn't "owned vs. unowned" — almost everything is owned. The line is:
            <em class="italic text-mist-700">does the owner profit from your answer?</em>
            Amazon, Comcast/WB and the PE firms do. Xperi and Cinegraph don't. Wordmarks shown for editorial comparison; ownership facts are cited in the table below.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      
<!-- ============================ SCOREBOARD TABLE ============================ -->
      <section
        id="scoreboard"
        class="scroll-mt-20 border-b border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 py-16 lg:py-24"
      >
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-6 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10">
          <div class="reveal max-w-3xl">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-mist-500">
              The receipts
            </div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-[34px] italic leading-[1.08] tracking-[-.01em] text-mist-950 sm:text-[48px]">
              Who owns the scoreboard?
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
              The killer column is the second one. Hover any cell with a dotted underline for the citation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal mt-10 overflow-x-auto rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-100">
            <table class="w-full min-w-[760px] border-collapse text-left">
