<!-- ============================ TWO FAILURES + PROVENANCE ============================ -->
      <section id="different" class="scroll-mt-20 py-16 lg:py-24">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-6 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10">
          <div class="reveal max-w-3xl">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-mist-500">
              Two failures, one moment
            </div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-[34px] italic leading-[1.08] tracking-[-.01em] text-mist-950 sm:text-[48px]">
              The number is broken. The owner isn't yours.
            </h2>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal mt-10 grid gap-3 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-6 lg:p-8">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[.14em] text-mist-500">
                Failure 01 — the signal
              </div>
              <h3 class="mt-3 font-display text-[26px] italic text-mist-950">
                Rigged by AI and bots.
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
                Every mainstream rating is an average of anonymous, unverifiable strangers. In 2026 that "crowd" plausibly includes bots, review-farms, brigades and AI agents that generate unlimited plausible reviews on demand.
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-[13.5px] text-mist-700">
                <li class="flex gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-rose-500"></span>You can't tell a cinephile's half-star from a botnet's.
                </li>
                <li class="flex gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-rose-500"></span>Review-bombing and astroturf are routine, not edge cases.
                </li>
                <li class="flex gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-rose-500"></span>LLM-written reviews are indistinguishable from human ones, free, at scale.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-5 border-l-2 border-mist-950/30 pl-3 font-display text-[18px] italic text-mist-950">
                A 7.4 across 100,000 votes measures whoever — or whatever — showed up.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-6 lg:p-8">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[.14em] text-mist-500">
                Failure 02 — the ownership
              </div>
              <h3 class="mt-3 font-display text-[26px] italic text-mist-950">
                Their agenda is not yours.
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
                The platforms holding these ratings are owned by the same giants whose products those ratings are meant to evaluate. There's no church and state — there's just the store.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
                Most started honestly — a fan database, a scrappy critic aggregator, a cinephile community. Then, one by one, they decided they loved money more than film, and they sold out.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-5 border-l-2 border-brand pl-3 font-display text-[18px] italic text-mist-950">
                Independence here is a phase, not a property. It lasts until the term sheet arrives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
<!-- positive turn -->
          <div class="reveal mt-14 max-w-3xl">
            <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-mist-500">
              How Cinegraph is different
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-4 font-display text-[28px] italic leading-tight text-mist-950 sm:text-[36px]">
              We don't trust random strangers. We show the evidence.
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
              A bot can manufacture a million ratings. It cannot manufacture a Cannes selection, a 40-year cultural footprint, or a place in the canon. Our evidence is expensive to fake. Theirs is free to fake.
            </p>
          </div>
          
<!-- provenance panel -->
          <div class="reveal prov mt-8 grid gap-6 rounded-[14px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.2fr] lg:p-8">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[.12em] text-mist-500">
                  How we know
                </div>
                <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[12px] font-semibold text-mist-900">
                  Cinegraph signal
                  <span class="inline-flex gap-1">
                    <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mist-950"></span><span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mist-950"></span><span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mist-950"></span><span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-mist-950"></span><span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full border border-mist-400"></span>
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-mist-500">high</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="mt-4 text-[13.5px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
                On every movie page, instead of one borrowed digit, we show
                <em class="italic">where the judgment comes from</em>
                — six independent lenses, each with the evidence behind it. No anonymous vote averages. No bot-fillable score.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-4 rounded-[8px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-100 p-3 text-[12.5px] leading-snug text-mist-600">
                ⓘ Thin evidence? We qualify or hide the number instead of faking authority. Want the raw numbers? <a
                  href="/movies"
                  class="font-semibold text-mist-950 underline"
                >Show the work</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-3.5">
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="78">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">🎭 Critics</span><span class="text-mist-500">38 sources</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-blue-500" style="--w:78%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="56">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">🏆 Festivals</span><span class="text-mist-500">Cannes '04 · 2 noms</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500" style="--w:56%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="88">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">📚 Canon / lists</span><span class="text-mist-500">1001 Movies · Sight &amp; Sound</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-purple-500" style="--w:88%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="67">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">🎬 Auteurs</span><span class="text-mist-500">Director + DP track record</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-orange-500" style="--w:67%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="74">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">⏳ Cultural pull</span><span class="text-mist-500">Durable over 20 yrs</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500" style="--w:74%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="prov-row" data-pct="31">
                <div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between text-[12.5px]">
                  <span class="font-medium text-mist-900">👥 Box office</span><span class="text-mist-500">Modest — and we say so</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-200">
                  <div class="prov-fill h-2 rounded-full bg-mist-500" style="--w:31%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
<!-- three differentiators -->
          <div class="reveal mt-3 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <div class="rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-5">
              <div class="font-display text-[30px] italic text-mist-950">01</div>
              <h4 class="mt-1 text-[15px] font-semibold text-mist-950">Evidence, not votes</h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-mist-600">
                Six named lenses, canon membership, festival lineage, durability over time — attributable and confidence-aware.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-5">
              <div class="font-display text-[30px] italic text-mist-950">02</div>
              <h4 class="mt-1 text-[15px] font-semibold text-mist-950">We didn't sell out</h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-mist-600">
                No studio, streamer, retailer or PE roll-up. No movies to push, no tickets to sell. Nothing you could rate well that makes us money.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-5">
              <div class="font-display text-[30px] italic text-mist-950">03</div>
              <h4 class="mt-1 text-[15px] font-semibold text-mist-950">
                One honest source: TMDb
              </h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-mist-600">
                Open, community-built factual data, owned by a party with no horse in the race. That's the bar. Amazon and Fandom don't clear it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
<!-- ============================ AGENDA STRIP ============================ -->
