<!-- ============================ SOLIDARITY + CTA ============================ -->
      <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-6 md:max-w-3xl lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-10">
          <div class="reveal mb-10 rounded-[12px] border border-mist-950/10 bg-mist-50 p-6 lg:p-7">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="text-[22px]">🌱</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-[20px] italic text-mist-950">
                  In solidarity with the Letterboxd community.
                </h3>
                <p class="mt-2 max-w-3xl text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-mist-700">
                  The people crowdfunding a buy-back are the good guys — allies, not targets. The villain is the structure: corporate and PE capture plus a bot-fillable signal. Community-funded film culture beats PE-owned film culture every time.
                </p>
